The paper focuses on dialogue understanding and representation learning, which are core topics in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses unsupervised pretraining tasks, which are related to unsupervised learning and representation learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions external knowledge integration, which is related to information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a mechanism for dialogue summarization/extraction, which is related to information extraction and text mining, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category.
